{"award_age":87.0,"bio_image":"full\/d3771fc4cdda8d689d7efed2afb5cb00ad9d7eb7.jpg","category":"Peace","country":"United Kingdom","date_of_birth":"1908-11-04T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":"2005-08-31T00:00:00.000Z","gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/4\/47\/Josef_Rotblat_ID_badge.png"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat","mini_bio":"<p><b>Sir Joseph (J\u00f3zef) Rotblat<\/b> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Order_of_St_Michael_and_St_George\" title=\"Order of St Michael and St George\">KCMG<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Order_of_the_British_Empire\" title=\"Order of the British Empire\">CBE<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society\" title=\"Fellow of the Royal Society\" class=\"mw-redirect\">FRS<\/a><sup id=\"cite_ref-frs_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat#cite_note-frs-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> (4 November 1908 \u2013 31 August 2005) was a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Poland\" title=\"Poland\">Polish<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Physicist\" title=\"Physicist\">physicist<\/a>, a self-described \"Pole with a British passport\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-passport_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat#cite_note-passport-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Rotblat was the only physicist to leave the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Manhattan_Project\" title=\"Manhattan Project\">Manhattan Project<\/a> (1942\u201346) on the grounds of conscience. Rotblat's work on <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nuclear_fallout\" title=\"Nuclear fallout\">nuclear fallout<\/a> was a major contribution toward the ratification of the 1963 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Partial_Nuclear_Test_Ban_Treaty\" title=\"Partial Nuclear Test Ban Treaty\">Partial Nuclear Test Ban Treaty<\/a>. A signatory of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Russell%E2%80%93Einstein_Manifesto\" title=\"Russell\u2013Einstein Manifesto\">Russell\u2013Einstein Manifesto<\/a> (1955), he was secretary-general of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pugwash_Conferences_on_Science_and_World_Affairs\" title=\"Pugwash Conferences on Science and World Affairs\">Pugwash Conferences on Science and World Affairs<\/a> from their founding until 1973. He shared, with the Pugwash Conferences, the 1995 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize<\/a> for efforts toward <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nuclear_disarmament\" title=\"Nuclear disarmament\">nuclear disarmament<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat#cite_note-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-scopus_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat#cite_note-scopus-8\"><span>[<\/span>8<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-retro_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat#cite_note-retro-9\"><span>[<\/span>9<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-dida_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat#cite_note-dida-10\"><span>[<\/span>10<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-googlescholar_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat#cite_note-googlescholar-11\"><span>[<\/span>11<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat#cite_note-12\"><span>[<\/span>12<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Joseph_Rotblat#cite_note-13\"><span>[<\/span>13<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a h